---
description: Enforce component architecture and separation of concerns in React/TypeScript
alwaysApply: false
globs: ["**/*.tsx", "**/*.ts", "!**/*.test.*", "!**/*.spec.*"]
---

## What This Rule Does

Enforces a strict separation of concerns across the React/TypeScript layer.
Components are presentational — they receive data and emit events. Hooks
own logic and side effects. The API layer owns all server communication.
Violating these boundaries produces code that is hard to test, hard to reuse,
and prone to data-fetching waterfalls and stale-state bugs.

**Memory references:** `memory-bank/architecture.md` (frontend module
boundaries), `memory-bank/frontendConventions.md` (state-decision tree this
rule enforces between useState/TanStack Query/Zustand/React Hook Form).

---

## Layer Model

```
pages/
  └── Route-level components. Compose feature modules. Zero business logic.
      Responsibility: layout, routing params, page title, auth guard.

features/[name]/
  ├── components/   Feature-scoped UI, may use local hooks and shared components
  ├── hooks/        Feature-scoped custom hooks (data fetching, local state machines)
  ├── api/          Feature API functions — fetchers only, no React Query here
  └── types/        Feature-scoped TypeScript interfaces

components/
  └── Shared, reusable, stateless UI. No API calls. No global state reads.
      Pure function of props. Tested in isolation. Documented in Storybook.

hooks/
  └── Shared custom hooks. Single responsibility. Return named object, not array.

api/
  └── All React Query hooks (useQuery / useMutation). All fetcher functions.
      All MSW handlers for tests. queryKeys.ts constant file.

store/
  └── Global client-only state (Zustand slices or Redux Toolkit slices).
      Never stores server cache — that lives in React Query's cache.

utils/
  └── Pure functions. Formatters, validators, transformers. No React imports.

types/
  └── Shared TypeScript interfaces and type aliases. api.ts for API shapes.
```

---

## Forbidden Patterns

### 1. Direct `fetch`/`axios` in Component Body
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
export function ProductList() {
  const [products, setProducts] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/products').then(r => r.json()).then(setProducts);
  }, []);
}

// ✅ CORRECT — fetcher in api/, React Query hook in hooks/ or api/
// api/products.ts
export async function getProducts(): Promise<Product[]> {
  const res = await apiClient.get<Product[]>('/products');
  return res.data;
}

// hooks/useProducts.ts (or features/catalog/hooks/useProducts.ts)
export function useProducts() {
  return useQuery({ queryKey: QUERY_KEYS.products.all, queryFn: getProducts });
}

// component
export function ProductList() {
  const { data: products = [], isLoading, isError } = useProducts();
  if (isLoading) return <ProductListSkeleton />;
  if (isError) return <ErrorMessage message="Failed to load products." />;
  return <ul>{products.map(p => <ProductItem key={p.id} product={p} />)}</ul>;
}
```

### 2. Business Logic in JSX / Render
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
export function OrderSummary({ order }: { order: Order }) {
  const tax = order.lines.reduce((sum, l) => sum + l.price * 0.15, 0);
  const eligible = order.lines.length > 0 && order.status === 'pending'
    && new Date() < new Date(order.expiresAt);
  return <div>{eligible ? <CheckoutButton tax={tax} /> : <ExpiredBadge />}</div>;
}

// ✅ CORRECT — extract to hook or util
function useOrderSummary(order: Order) {
  const tax = useMemo(() => order.lines.reduce((s, l) => s + l.price * TAX_RATE, 0), [order.lines]);
  const isEligibleForCheckout = useMemo(
    () => order.lines.length > 0 && order.status === 'pending' && new Date() < new Date(order.expiresAt),
    [order]
  );
  return { tax, isEligibleForCheckout };
}
```

### 3. Inline Props Interface
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION — interface buried inside component file, unreferenceable from tests/stories
export function Avatar({ size, src, alt }: { size: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'; src: string; alt: string }) {}

// ✅ CORRECT — defined above the component (or in types/ for shared components)
export interface AvatarProps {
  size: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  src: string;
  alt: string;
}
export function Avatar({ size, src, alt }: AvatarProps) {}
```

### 4. `any` Type
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
function parseResponse(data: any) { return data.items; }

// ✅ CORRECT
interface ApiListResponse<T> { items: T[]; total: number; }
function parseResponse<T>(data: unknown): T[] {
  const parsed = data as ApiListResponse<T>;
  return parsed.items;
}
```

### 5. Direct DOM Manipulation
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
document.getElementById('modal-root')!.style.display = 'block';

// ✅ CORRECT
const modalRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
useEffect(() => { if (open) modalRef.current?.focus(); }, [open]);
```

### 6. Side Effects in Component Body (Outside useEffect)
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION — runs on every render, not just on mount
export function Dashboard() {
  analytics.track('dashboard_viewed'); // side effect in render body
  return <DashboardContent />;
}

// ✅ CORRECT
useEffect(() => { analytics.track('dashboard_viewed'); }, []);
```

### 7. Mutating State Directly
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
const [items, setItems] = useState<Item[]>([]);
items.push(newItem); // mutates without triggering re-render
setItems(items);     // same reference — React may skip re-render

// ✅ CORRECT
setItems(prev => [...prev, newItem]);
```

### 8. `console.log` in Production Code
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
console.log('user data:', user); // leaks PII to browser console

// ✅ CORRECT — use a structured logger utility or remove entirely
logger.debug('User session established', { userId: user.id });
```

### 9. Hardcoded Strings in JSX
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
<button>Submit Order</button>
<p>Your order has been placed successfully.</p>

// ✅ CORRECT — constants file or i18n key
<button>{t('order.submitButton')}</button>
<p>{t('order.successMessage')}</p>
```

### 10. Component > 200 Lines
```
// ❌ VIOLATION — CheckoutPage.tsx is 380 lines
// ✅ CORRECT — split into:
//   CheckoutPage.tsx           (route-level, ~40 lines)
//   features/checkout/components/OrderSummaryPanel.tsx
//   features/checkout/components/ShippingForm.tsx
//   features/checkout/components/PaymentSection.tsx
//   features/checkout/hooks/useCheckout.ts
```

### 11. Prop Drilling > 2 Levels
```
// ❌ VIOLATION: Page → Section → Panel → Widget → Button all receive `onOrderComplete`
// ✅ CORRECT: Lift to Zustand slice, React Query mutation cache, or Context at the Section level
```

### 12. `useEffect` with Missing / Suppressed Dependencies
```tsx
// ❌ VIOLATION
useEffect(() => {
  fetchUser(userId); // eslint-disable-next-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps
}, []); // userId missing from deps — stale closure bug

// ✅ CORRECT
useEffect(() => { fetchUser(userId); }, [userId]);
// If fetchUser is stable, wrap in useCallback first
```

